The paper deals with the logical complexity of proofs in cyclic arithmetic, which is a topic in mathematical logic. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves proof theoretic techniques and structural manipulations, which are relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of normal forms and the study of fragments of cyclic arithmetic suggest cs.PL (Programming Languages) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves results on the reverse mathematics of Buchi's theorem, which is related to cs.IT (Information Theory).
